{{ITALIC}}It is expected that many Mix & Match {{ITALIC}}Matches{{/ITALIC}} will have last-second “buzzer-beater” moments. The key moment occurs when the timer display shows 0:00. At many events, a buzzer sound will also play at T=0:00; however, the {{ITALIC}}Field{{/ITALIC}} timer display takes precedence in the event of any audio discrepancies. If a {{ITALIC}}Stack{{/ITALIC}} is released from a {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} before this moment, it will be allowed to finish its path and the score will be calculated once it comes to rest. However, if it is released after this moment (i.e., the {{ITALIC}}Robot{{/ITALIC}} was still moving past T=0:00) it will not count and the {{ITALIC}}Team{{/ITALIC}} will receive a {{ITALIC}}Violation{{/ITALIC}} as described below. In cases where a last-second scoring attempt is “too close to call,” {{ITALIC}}Teams{{/ITALIC}} will generally be given the “benefit of the doubt” and the score will be counted. {{ITALIC}}Teams{{/ITALIC}} are advised to {{ITALIC}}Place{{/ITALIC}} and release {{ITALIC}}Stacks{{/ITALIC}} a second or two before the timer reaches zero to avoid the need for referee judgment calls.{{/ITALIC}}
Violation Notes: 
• Because scoring that happens after the {{ITALIC}}Match{{/ITALIC}} is not counted, all {{ITALIC}}Violations{{/ITALIC}} of <GG12> should be recorded as {{ITALIC}}Minor Violations{{/ITALIC}}. 
• If a {{ITALIC}}Team{{/ITALIC}} receives three {{ITALIC}}Minor Violations{{/ITALIC}} within the same event, all future <GG12> {{ITALIC}}Violations{{/ITALIC}} at that event will be considered {{ITALIC}}Major Violations{{/ITALIC}} and {{ITALIC}}Disqualifications{{/ITALIC}}. 
